<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<!--@import "_head.kit"-->

<body>
    <!--@import "_header.kit"-->

    <main>
        <article class="project-detail project-case-study">
            <section class="case-cover section-fade" aria-label="Project cover">
                <a href="/portfolio.html" class="back-link">Back to portfolio</a>
                <figure class="case-study-image case-study-image-cover">
                    <img src="assets\images\projects\mova-wireframe-01@1x.jpg "
                        srcset="assets\images\projects\mova-wireframe-01@1x.jpg, assets\images\projects\mova-wireframe-01@2x.jpg 2x"
                        width="1800" height="1100" alt="Placeholder cover slide for the MOVA case study" loading="eager"
                        decoding="async">
                </figure>
            </section>

            <header class="case-intro section-fade">
                <div class="container case-intro-grid">
                    <div class="case-title-block">
                        <p class="eyebrow">Product Design Case Study</p>
                        <h1>MOVA: Optimizing the In-Store Installment Financing Journey</h1>
                        <p class="lead">A professional case focused on improving an assisted sales flow used by store
                            operators to offer financial products in a retail environment.</p>
                    </div>
                    <aside class="case-info-panel" aria-label="Project information">
                        <dl>
                            <div>
                                <dt>Date</dt>
                                <dd>September 2024</dd>
                            </div>
                            <div>
                                <dt>Deadline</dt>
                                <dd>Pilot delivery timeline</dd>
                            </div>
                            <div>
                                <dt>Team context</dt>
                                <dd>9 members</dd>
                            </div>
                            <div>
                                <dt>Context</dt>
                                <dd>Professional project</dd>
                            </div>
                        </dl>
                    </aside>
                </div>
            </header>

            <section class="case-section case-resume">
                <div class="container case-text-grid">
                    <div class="case-section-label">
                        <p class="eyebrow">Resume</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="case-copy">
                        <h2>Simplifying a complex financial decision inside an assisted retail journey.</h2>
                        <p>The work combined journey mapping, behavioral funnel analysis, operator research, business
                            rules and cross-functional collaboration to simplify an in-store installment financing flow.
                        </p>
                        <p>The strategic relevance of the case was not only interface clarity. It was a B2B2C service
                            experience involving the customer, the operator, the retailer and the bank.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </section>

            <section class="case-section">
                <div class="container case-text-grid">
                    <div class="case-section-label">
                        <p class="eyebrow">Context</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="case-copy">
                        <h2>Retail credit journeys depend on trust, clarity and operator confidence.</h2>
                        <p>In Brazil, department store credit cards operate as more than payment instruments. They are
                            connected to credit, insurance, loyalty and financial services.</p>
                        <p>Inside this ecosystem, the store operator plays a key role: explaining the offer, handling
                            objections and helping the customer make a real-time financial decision.</p>
                        <div class="case-image-grid case-image-grid-two">
                            <figure class="case-study-image">
                                <img src="/assets/images/projects/project-1-context-01@1x.jpg"
                                    srcset="/assets/images/projects/project-1-context-01@1x.jpg 1x, /assets/images/projects/project-1-context-01@2x.jpg 2x"
                                    width="1200" height="800" alt="Placeholder slide for MOVA context image 01"
                                    loading="lazy" decoding="async">
                                <figcaption>Context image 01</figcaption>
                            </figure>
                            <figure class="case-study-image">
                                <img src="/assets/images/projects/project-1-context-02@1x.jpg"
                                    srcset="/assets/images/projects/project-1-context-02@1x.jpg 1x, /assets/images/projects/project-1-context-02@2x.jpg 2x"
                                    width="1200" height="800" alt="Placeholder slide for MOVA context image 02"
                                    loading="lazy" decoding="async">
                                <figcaption>Context image 02</figcaption>
                            </figure>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </section>

            <section class="case-section case-problem">
                <div class="container">
                    <div class="problem-card">
                        <p class="eyebrow">The Problem / How Might We</p>
                        <h2>The journey needed to become simpler without losing trust, clarity or control.</h2>
                        <p>The problem was not just interface complexity. It was a service experience with operational
                            pressure, customer decision-making and financial business rules happening at the same time.
                        </p>
                        <blockquote>
                            How might we make the installment payment flow simpler and more efficient for operators,
                            without losing clarity for customers in a debt-restructuring moment?
                        </blockquote>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </section>

            <section class="case-section">
                <div class="container case-text-grid">
                    <div class="case-section-label">
                        <p class="eyebrow">Challenges</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="case-copy">
                        <h2>Balancing operational efficiency with a sensitive financial decision.</h2>
                        <p>The main challenge was reducing unnecessary steps while keeping the information
                            understandable for operators and customers. The flow had to support assisted sales, business
                            rules and compliance without making the experience feel heavier.</p>
                        <figure class="case-study-image case-study-image-wide">
                            <img src="/assets/images/projects/project-1-challenges-01@1x.jpg"
                                srcset="/assets/images/projects/project-1-challenges-01@1x.jpg 1x, /assets/images/projects/project-1-challenges-01@2x.jpg 2x"
                                width="1600" height="1000" alt="Placeholder slide for MOVA challenges image 01"
                                loading="lazy" decoding="async">
                            <figcaption>Challenges image 01</figcaption>
                        </figure>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </section>

            <section class="case-section">
                <div class="container case-text-grid">
                    <div class="case-section-label">
                        <p class="eyebrow">Solution</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="case-copy">
                        <h2>A clearer assisted-sales flow aligned with real store behavior.</h2>
                        <p>I contributed across the research, analysis and journey optimization process, mapping the
                            physical journey inside Magalu stores and the digital journey inside the assisted channel.
                        </p>
                        <p>The solution focused on reducing unnecessary steps, improving clarity in key decision moments
                            and aligning the interface with the reality of assisted sales.</p>
                        <div class="case-image-grid case-image-grid-two">
                            <figure class="case-study-image">
                                <img src="/assets/images/projects/project-1-solution-01@1x.jpg"
                                    srcset="/assets/images/projects/project-1-solution-01@1x.jpg 1x, /assets/images/projects/project-1-solution-01@2x.jpg 2x"
                                    width="1200" height="800" alt="Placeholder slide for MOVA solution image 01"
                                    loading="lazy" decoding="async">
                                <figcaption>Solution image 01</figcaption>
                            </figure>
                            <figure class="case-study-image">
                                <img src="/assets/images/projects/project-1-solution-02@1x.jpg"
                                    srcset="/assets/images/projects/project-1-solution-02@1x.jpg 1x, /assets/images/projects/project-1-solution-02@2x.jpg 2x"
                                    width="1200" height="800" alt="Placeholder slide for MOVA solution image 02"
                                    loading="lazy" decoding="async">
                                <figcaption>Solution image 02</figcaption>
                            </figure>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </section>

            <section class="case-section">
                <div class="container case-text-grid">
                    <div class="case-section-label">
                        <p class="eyebrow">Results</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="case-copy">
                        <h2>Impact was measured through speed, clarity and pilot readiness.</h2>
                        <p>The project used indicators such as SLA time, experience checklist, reduced journey screens
                            and pilot completion rate to evaluate the improved journey.</p>
                        <figure class="case-study-image case-study-image-wide">
                            <img src="/assets/images/projects/project-1-results-01@1x.jpg"
                                srcset="/assets/images/projects/project-1-results-01@1x.jpg 1x, /assets/images/projects/project-1-results-01@2x.jpg 2x"
                                width="1600" height="1000" alt="Placeholder slide for MOVA results image 01"
                                loading="lazy" decoding="async">
                            <figcaption>Results image 01</figcaption>
                        </figure>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </section>

            <section class="case-section">
                <div class="container case-text-grid">
                    <div class="case-section-label">
                        <p class="eyebrow">Closing</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="case-copy">
                        <h2>A service-design case about making complexity easier to act on.</h2>
                        <p>The strongest learning was that assisted financial journeys are shaped by more than screens.
                            They depend on timing, operator confidence, business constraints and the clarity of the
                            conversation happening in the store.</p>
                        <figure class="case-study-image case-study-image-wide">
                            <img src="/assets/images/projects/project-1-closing-01@1x.jpg"
                                srcset="/assets/images/projects/project-1-closing-01@1x.jpg 1x, /assets/images/projects/project-1-closing-01@2x.jpg 2x"
                                width="1600" height="1000" alt="Placeholder slide for MOVA closing image 01"
                                loading="lazy" decoding="async">
                            <figcaption>Closing image 01</figcaption>
                        </figure>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </section>

            <section class="case-section case-role">
                <div class="container case-role-card">
                    <div>
                        <p class="eyebrow">My Role</p>
                        <h2>Product Analyst / Journey Mapping / Funnel Analysis / Research</h2>
                    </div>
                    <div class="role-list">
                        <p>I supported journey mapping, Google Analytics funnel analysis, shadowing, stakeholder
                            interviews, service design and business rules mapping.</p>
                        <p>My strongest involvement was connecting operational evidence, behavioral data and
                            cross-functional input into a clearer assisted-sales journey.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </section>
        </article>
    </main>

    <!--@import "_footer.kit"-->
</body>

</html>

